    "body": "Problem: No built-in way to show LSP hover info or diagnostics when the mouse hovers over a symbol or diagnostic.\r\n\r\nSolution: Add vim.lsp.mouse module with enable()/is_enabled(). Uses <MouseMove> with debounce to show diagnostic floats or LSP hover at the mouse position. Preserves existing user <MouseMove> mappings.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/262ed2a2-5bab-4993-bbb9-f02927a0ae4b\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-11T13:29:57Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Seems potentially useful, but I'm wondering if it should be more generic, similar to `:Inspect` and `vim.ui.open()` which handle \"things at cursor\" rather than being LSP-specific.\r\n\r\nI also would request again that we consider generalizing a \"debounce\" internal util before doing it yet another time for this special purpose. \r\n\r\nYou have 34 PRs open, please focus on keeping them updated and getting a few of them in mergeable condition https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pulls/glepnir",
            "created_at": "2026-04-11T13:29:57Z",
